snippet.textDisplay: @Daniel Gibson I'm Australian. No offence, but the US has much less freedom than many developed countries. I could make a case to convince you, but it would be too long. One point is that America thinks of "freedom" as individual choice. That's why you can't pull together as a country. Any form of collectivism is rejected as being "socialist" but in some areas such as labour laws and healthcare collectivism would take a great burden off many people ie. collectivism in these areas would give people greater freedom from struggle and worry. A more secure, healthier population would be less disillusioned and more inclined to be supportive of governments and  more likely to pull together
